						<img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/211dffd3c25f504a57e01ac5bac29726?s=32&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/211dffd3c25f504a57e01ac5bac29726?s=64&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-32 photo' height='32' width='32' loading='lazy' decoding='async'/>						<b class="fn">John L Smith Jr.</b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="https://allthingsliberty.com/2018/05/the-first-countries-to-diplomatically-recognize-the-united-states/#comment-113912"><time datetime="2018-05-16T12:09:58-04:00">May 16, 2018 at 12:09 pm</time></a>					</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Gene, you very well summed up the diplomatic  combination that, &#8220;both formal diplomatic recognition and trade agreements were vital to establishing the US as a sovereign nation.&#8221;</p>
