		<li id="comment-127554" class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
			<article id="div-comment-127554" class="comment-body">
				<footer class="comment-meta">
					<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/c87aeca5268e9906418fd2aebe78de38?s=32&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/c87aeca5268e9906418fd2aebe78de38?s=64&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-32 photo' height='32' width='32' loading='lazy' decoding='async'/>						<b class="fn">kornelis</b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="https://allthingsliberty.com/2018/05/the-first-countries-to-diplomatically-recognize-the-united-states/#comment-127554"><time datetime="2019-10-02T23:35:03-04:00">October 2, 2019 at 11:35 pm</time></a>					</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Fort Oranje is without a doubt the most impressive stronghold on St. Eustatius. On November 16, 1776 this structure made world headlines when it fired a couple of friendly welcome shots to a flag no one had ever seen beyond the 13 colonies. It was the newly created symbol of the self-proclaimed United States of America. The garrison at Fort Oranje was actually the first foreign port to formally acknowledge the flag of this new born nation.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

				<div class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-127554' data-commentid="127554" data-postid="16178" data-belowelement="div-comment-127554" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to kornelis" aria-label='Reply to kornelis'>Reply</a></div>			</article><!-- .comment-body -->
