		<li id="comment-136316" class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1">
			<article id="div-comment-136316" class="comment-body">
				<footer class="comment-meta">
					<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9b73acb7d61361866ec864d277754df2?s=32&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9b73acb7d61361866ec864d277754df2?s=64&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-32 photo' height='32' width='32' loading='lazy' decoding='async'/>						<b class="fn">Oumaima</b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="https://allthingsliberty.com/2018/05/the-first-countries-to-diplomatically-recognize-the-united-states/#comment-136316"><time datetime="2020-08-06T21:21:24-04:00">August 6, 2020 at 9:21 pm</time></a>					</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>This is a very late comment anyway &#8230;.</p>
<p>The kingdom of Morocco acknowledged USA in the 20th of December 1777 under the reign of Sultan Mohamed III, making it the first country in the world to acknowledge USA. The first American embassy (which was called the &#8220;American Legation&#8221;) to open somewhere in the world opened in Morocco in Tangier which is now a museum. In 1786 a treaty of peace and friendship was signed between the two countries and it is still on until today. </p>
<p>France was next after Morocco, not the first one.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

